text: Alexeyevka () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Chukadybashevsky Selsoviet, Tuymazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 257 as of 2010. There are 6 streets. == Geography == It is located 54 km from Tuymazy. == References == Category:Rural localities in Tuymazinsky District
title: Alexeyevka, Tuymazinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
